Notebook[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism, by Computation", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"2d11ce87-965d-494d-ae98-28fd13d6f7e9"],

Cell["\<\
This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it at \
a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"08703da0-84f8-46ff-aaa8-22c3272f8357"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arc is: a state is what stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "76906e6a-73e9-4af1-ac33-3507a919e73a"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3953d7e5-187a-435b-9bcf-1c4c3be13684"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ae6f65d3-b0b8-49b7-bb0d-12ad37bbb144"],
 " (the field of two elements ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], 
   RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
   RowBox[{"1", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4170ae90-0309-43c8-9cb5-8fda808a626c"],
 " with all arithmetic done mod 2, so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "+", "1", "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9bfb2e3a-80cb-433a-a5cb-fec4f2a073f8"],
 " and vector addition is the bitwise XOR), and then scale, codes, and the \
frontier. The audience is graduate students who know quantum mechanics and \
the Pauli group but have not yet seen why a stabilizer state of a thousand \
qubits is something you can hold in your hand. Everything below is built \
explicitly so you can change it, break it, and extend it. The Wolfram \
QuantumFramework symbols we exercise live in the Wolfram QuantumFramework \
paclet; the central one is PauliStabilizer."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"10ef011e-d690-46b8-9465-9424023cce5f"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7809606a-a279-4dcd-b2a8-5d6143ab1c42"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Needs"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "99ff7171-11e5-46fb-8a04-3f2fbc4c5ff6"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"27b0e292-b4cc-44c0-833b-4ab7c990b947"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "PacletDirectoryLoad", 
   "[", "\"\</Users/mohammadb/Documents/GitHub/QuantumFramework/\
QuantumFramework\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"1da3f8bf-b914-479d-bc20-3392abd5a96f"],

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5a0e1a49-14ff-4237-9278-61e95d6a7293"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context later; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"819a7e2e-fc47-4d04-95cf-cf22a04fa487"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "84289d1e-3a66-4578-af35-a4d64ee0052d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"6926446b-18ab-42e4-8328-feabab41ca1f"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"686c0971-7deb-4a48-bada-168fda41d5e4"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"d4710e6c-7a44-40cb-9575-7ccc05be2c60"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2f138a0a-f016-4fd7-b120-be48c06bd1f1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 " one at a time: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"546f0740-d955-49a9-bc88-24579b31d247"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"516d7301-dba7-4d15-85c0-441761781485"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"865d3831-f260-4dfc-944e-6cbea1e697b8"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"1c9fe4fc-abf7-4770-b98c-69bf5c5f0dab"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SWAP\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"36319b31-47c2-4702-bf8d-64e01821443f"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"074473df-973e-4c2e-ae56-f9c001a559c7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a whole circuit", "TI"],
 " as a gate list, routed through the compiled engine (bare names take \
default targets, ",
 Cell[BoxData["->"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "50704dd6-1f9f-414b-902a-99d7feeda09c"],
 " sets explicit ones): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"ebeecb51-4d97-4955-b397-c30a609164db"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b59d3b0e-bb13-404c-9936-44ead955f661"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Inspect", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"ee58fadb-d707-450f-afa2-66aef15505fe"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Tableau\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"dd21f48a-1b59-4775-8596-5f78eba7cb51"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ee5b5c32-a9e6-47be-9ea7-601839caa261"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<State\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "572a289c-5880-47ad-a032-cea790eadf2d"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9b2f8999-2e24-4c2c-9416-bc7d48833cfa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Measure", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"3c3062d4-9838-4d40-89a4-c70e2081c1c5"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"b6ce266b-9cec-4174-ab8a-b01a30bf932e"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Expectation\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"4c15872f-108e-4778-9092-2496a4116a62"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SymbolicMeasure\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"0248ca9c-1771-4127-9b7a-ca0e4a677d21"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6fb3bfd3-a48f-4472-9fd7-2228d0324a92"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Entanglement entropy", "TI"],
 " across a cut: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"e69a4a9e-881d-4f0b-9596-898bb897bc44"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"35f6760b-944a-4e6b-bb95-22ce0dec7e3f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Sibling heads", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "StabilizerFrame"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b9fba14c-179c-4a76-96cc-f5633f394a30"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "CliffordChannel"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "61786c0d-f1f2-4f20-9d7f-3dd8fdb8b14b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "GraphState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ec3bd842-b4ed-4644-a012-74e2d85718ba"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "LocalComplement"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bded3e68-6427-4a87-b62f-db2b47259089"],
 ", and the predicate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "StabilizerStateQ"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ff0015aa-10e3-4010-b7a6-d2785542f5b2"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"cec75936-ed83-4073-9f0f-745166d0da55"],

Cell["Why stabilizers: the exponential wall", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"93394a2b-481e-4f2c-8197-5f32bfc345d7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure state of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ae0546b9-77c8-452a-8e8d-e4ac199fbd8c"],
 " qubits is a unit vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\:2102", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "acf3dd45-65bc-49b4-9043-7a5083f65f2c"],
 ", so writing it down means storing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2c05bcb8-d004-4637-b1b0-dd1a9b3e151f"],
 " complex amplitudes. At ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "20"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4a87c4eb-528b-43da-9465-152f99031cb6"],
 " that is already a million numbers; at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "50"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dca50bfe-ea00-4f51-b039-41670c5f8321"],
 " it is about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["10", "15"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0849822a-539b-4440-ab83-f7a6d5bc5504"],
 ", a petabyte of amplitudes even at one byte each; by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "100"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "807222c3-ea8b-4c76-b4c0-4b6da3a1192d"],
 " it passes the number of atoms in a building (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Tilde]", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", "30"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cdb6d509-16ee-4782-a1bd-25e679dff276"],
 "). Yet many of the states we care most about, including every state any \
error-correcting code protects, are not generic: they sit at the fixed points \
of a large group of Pauli operators, and that structure can be stored in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d107a9a2-dac8-43f6-b3fb-2a60b179a84d"],
 " bits."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9d593c7d-a0fb-4054-8826-7907794b286a"],

Cell["\<\
To feel the wall, ask for the dense state vector of a 20-qubit GHZ state and \
look only at its length:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc53540f-8572-4c07-a224-a28d84415377"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Length", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "20", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"ff4da540-d82b-4463-9717-828172b8b1c6"],

Cell[BoxData["1048576"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"e17f6efd-185b-4c61-b400-d78de792286b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "20"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "57358c31-2499-4fe4-9a52-bfba9b53d286"],
 " amplitudes for a state that, as we will see, is pinned down completely by \
20 short Pauli strings. The stabilizer formalism is the bookkeeping that \
exploits exactly this gap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"27ed3cc1-a34f-47b6-b42c-654936b86ee4"],

Cell["A state is what fixes it: the single qubit", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c9139dab-5c2b-479e-a097-c3cca5152356"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The central move is to stop describing a state by its amplitudes and start \
describing it by the operators that leave it invariant. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "afa9911d-0907-4580-8802-7cb19ec3a348"],
 " is the unique ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "939c9c3e-0b18-477d-8ef2-8b9e4b671d29"],
 " eigenvector of the Pauli operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fcfaf1a1-3dbb-484e-a12b-66e3e207428d"],
 ". We say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fbd7f02a-22dc-4907-981b-ccc387c17a61"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["stabilizes", "TI"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3b8cb42a-4fe2-4f79-a4a2-a106e892ee22"],
 ", and since one operator already determines a one-qubit state up to \
normalization, that single fact ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the state."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1a823a5b-d99b-4479-9b24-0663a9a7e43c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A caution that defines the whole subject: this works only for special \
states. Of all one-qubit pure states, exactly six are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "af603025-680a-4ad9-a106-8552ce1227d0"],
 " eigenstates of a Pauli: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e9cba9f9-c22b-4b48-a1a5-195d19a8f3c3"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4c6c54db-45f3-411a-ad27-78e1fb748790"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "729cd83a-5fb9-4504-8c0b-2dd873dce7ad"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"\[PlusMinus]"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7bef2500-fdd4-47af-a548-7efbe13f1fd0"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9fcd5927-b166-4d61-80b8-8919ea90641c"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["i", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "628d1a82-72b7-4615-b084-38f24c257a8c"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1b9dcbdd-177f-4688-9ad8-eba27f705a4d"],
 ". These six are the ",
 StyleBox["stabilizer states", "TI"],
 ", and the formalism is exactly their theory and its multi-qubit \
generalization; a generic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "38a6c86d-cc22-414f-921d-ef473b0a6762"],
 " is fixed by no Pauli and falls outside it. What makes the restriction \
worth a whole subject is that the states it does cover, as the next sections \
show, include the ones error correction and large parts of quantum algorithms \
are built from."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e09a85e6-42ae-4eac-b5d5-6d6ccded752f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "32c09991-98fc-499e-961b-7877448bb201"],
 " fixes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "74864fb1-232b-432e-962e-0b889b4707d1"],
 ", recalling that the built-in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a613c231-0d17-4a3d-9a82-ff54e9b1b668"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "1bd9f446-daa1-4dc6-a758-1135f6215b8d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "40e4d3f3-5527-4a65-81d9-09be345ae149"],
 " are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "381cce32-673a-4815-9527-737db29d5b6c"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b99923f4-2b1e-4769-913f-e7c031eb4d5a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c16521db-acc1-4acc-916e-e7a740be6d0e"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d8390104-b5ba-46fc-9038-5c0e1139d33a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}], " ", "==", " ", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"54b98aa3-500e-41a1-bf54-fd5bd7a819ba"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"f02e45e0-4346-41e7-b39a-cbd420f3b620"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the framework, the one-qubit register ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5a5a9b2d-60ca-4d81-9297-6c1b1ca1e477"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "6a686731-18b6-410d-9d83-27d394523fb4"],
 ". The object prints as a summary box that shows its generators and, for \
small systems, its tableau, so the cheap representation is the thing you \
see:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"344a25bc-67a8-4216-9fcb-f8ec1943f0f5"],

